Mbe e gbun na pini ni, ŋgi na hin? E leele gbo, mu sɛɛnlɛ nyjɛ e pe yire tɛɛ mu eyɛ tɔ nɛɛrɛ ni. Yire titi tia e ble nyu to, a e yɛlɛ nyjɛ ee li kɔ. Mbe ti mbe waŋgrɛ yire na e pini mbra tɛɛ, mbra e tɛɛlɛ.
Pra lopom wre mɛɛ tɛɛ Oholah, mna ble wre mɛɛ tɛɛ Oholibah. Oholah yire mu Samaria ŋga, a Oholibah yire mu Jerusalem ŋga. Ni chiɛlɛ na lɛ, a pra bibilɛ, na bichiɛlɛ se mu ni ŋga.
Kena kee ŋga o Tafun Nyiɛkpɔɔ Jaŋgafun wre yuu yi kre, ŋga mu ni kee fɛɛ, mu krɔ kna mu wa ni na ŋga, mu mu niŋge tiɛrɛɛ kre kanyana nya.”
Ta jiin lɛɛ brɛmm, a maashia ŋmba u ku wre kumu pe. A maashia namu laa mu ndra na, ndee mbe kpawrɛ wɔ jeelee na, a maashia yira tɛɛ mbe mu yiɛ tapan haa tɔ, ndee mbe paala sro ŋga kumu pefɛɛnlɛ lii kre ka le nyuu.”
Pie pan mbe Tyre kakpɔɔ mboe yire juari mbe wo, mbe ki nyinyi gedenyi nyjɛ na pe yire na chia kre sri yire juari, mbe ni ki juaraa yire pɔ mbe sɛ wo, mbe ki kro dnɛ yire waara.
